de.modlab.smilib.main
Class SmilesParser2

java.lang.Object
  de.modlab.smilib.main.SmilesParser2

public class SmilesParser2
extends java.lang.Object

Parses a SMILES string and an AtomContainer. The full SSMILES subset and the '%' tag for more than 10 rings at a time are supported. An example: 

 try {
   SmilesParser sp = new SmilesParser();
   Molecule m = sp.parseSmiles("c1ccccc1");
 } catch (InvalidSmilesException ise) {
 }

This parser does not parse stereochemical information, but the following features are supported: reaction smiles, partitioned structures, charged atoms, implicit hydrogen count, '*' and isotope information.

See for further information.
